</picture></div></div><div
class="block-intro-text"><p>Opening a pizzeria can be a profitable investment, especially when you’ve prepared correctly. However, while the pizza industry is growing, it remains an extremely competitive and saturated market. We've developed a step-by-step guide to help you start a successful pizza business.</p></div></div></div></div><div
class="section-content"><div
class="container"><div
class="narrow-container"><div
class="block"><p><strong>There is a growing demand for pizza in the U.S. and internationally.</strong> According to an <a
href="https://www.statista.com/topics/1610/pizza-delivery-market/#topicOverview">industry report</a>, the pizza industry showed an all-time high of $46.9 billion in U.S. sales in 2022. There were <a
href="https://www.ibisworld.com/united-states/market-research-reports/pizza-restaurants-industry/#IndustryStatisticsAndTrends">more than 78,000 pizza businesses</a> in the U.S. in 2023, and the industry is expected to see <a
href="https://www.businessresearchinsights.com/market-reports/pizzas-market-102575">annual growth of 10.89% from 2023 to 2031</a>.</p><p><strong>Technology is playing a much bigger role in the industry.</strong> Research shows that social media, online ordering, and delivery technology are giving brands a competitive edge.</p></div><div
class="block block-download"><div
class="download-wrapper"><div
class="row align-items-center"><div
class="col-md-4 order-md-2"><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
