owever, a <a href=\"https:\/\/www.pmq.com\/pizza-power-report-2023\/\">2023 report<\/a> shows that independents are making a comeback, even though they are hindered slightly by inflation in food cost, leading to a necessary hike in pizza prices, which in turn leads to a decrease in sales. Sales for independents jumped by 10.24% in 2022, while franchises saw a slight drop of 1.5% in sales between October 2020 and September 2021.<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p>Independent ownership means that all the responsibilities fall on you, from creating the menu to building a brand and a positive reputation. You will have more control over the budget and will keep all the profits, but you will carry more of the initial costs of starting up. You will also have more control over branding, menu changes, employment structure, and ambiance but, without a track record of success, it is difficult to attract investors or source start-up funding.<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p>With a franchise, a proven concept, established brand and reputation, clear marketing strategy, and business concept are all handed to you. There is often a franchising fee of up to several hundred thousand dollars, royalties and national advertising campaign fees, and proof of startup funding, but the business and menu guidelines have already been developed. However, you will have very little control over menu items and decor. Franchises do generally source financial support more easily because of their proven track records.<\/p>\n"}]},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"2","name":"<p>Decide what type of pizza shop you want to open.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>There are four main types of pizza shops: delivery, take-out, take 'n' bake, and dine-in. Each type of pizzeria offers a different range of services and attracts different customers. Each one has different startup and management needs.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.notzarla.com/guides/how-to-open-a-pizza-shop#how-to-open-a-pizza-shop-section1-step2","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-decide-what-pizza-shop-you-want-to-open-288x288-20200817.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"},"itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p><strong>Delivery pizza shops<\/strong> deliver pizzas to customers after orders are made online or on the telephone. Costs of insurance and delivery driver safety are major concerns, but customers will ultimately pay the increased cost of delivery.<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p><strong>Take-out pizza shops<\/strong> offer take-out pizza over the counter. These establishments are often small, require fewer staff, no waiters, very little tableware and furniture, and less equipment.<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p>A <strong>take 'n' bake<\/strong> offers the same services as a take-out but has even less equipment needs, as customers buy the pre-made pizza to bake at home. It does need more refrigeration and display cases.<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p><strong>Dine-in pizza shops<\/strong> are your typical pizza restaurants. It is the most expensive of the lot, requiring extensive kitchen equipment, furniture, tableware, music, lighting, waiters, etc.<\/p>\n"}]}]},{"@type":"HowToSection","position":"2","name":"<p>Write out a business plan.<\/p>\n","itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"1","name":"<p>Do the necessary research.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>In order to write out your business plan, you will need to research your top competitors as well as the pizza market in your area. You will also want to research your customer base to find out what kind of pizza shop they would be more inclined to visit and the types of pizza they would enjoy the most.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.notzarla.com/guides/how-to-open-a-pizza-shop#how-to-open-a-pizza-shop-section2-step1","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-research-your-competitors-288x288-20200811_2020-08-11-134856.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"}},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"2","name":"<p>Include all the essentials in your business plan.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>A business plan should describe your pizza business and brand, show how your pizzeria will grow, define what it will need to succeed, and outline possible challenges it is likely to face. This business plan is a sort of road map for you in the early stages and it can be used to get financing and attract partners.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.notzarla.com/guides/how-to-open-a-pizza-shop#how-to-open-a-pizza-shop-section2-step2","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-create-a-business-plan-288x288-20200724.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"},"itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToTip","text":"<p>Essentials for a pizza shop business plan include an executive summary, industry overview, market analysis, sales and marketing plan, ownership and management plan, operating plan, and financial plan.<\/p>\n"}]}]},{"@type":"HowToSection","position":"3","name":"<p>Choose a business name.<\/p>\n","itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"1","name":"<p>Try using a business name generator.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>We recommend <a href=\"https:\/\/www.namesnack.com\/\">NameSnack<\/a>, a free online-based name generator that uses AI to come up with thousands of potential names. With NameSnack, users can also do an instant domain name availability search.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.notzarla.com/guides/how-to-open-a-pizza-shop#how-to-open-a-pizza-shop-section3-step1","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-use-a-name-generator-288x288-20200703.png?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"}},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"2","name":"<p>Conduct a trademark search.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>A trademark search with the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.uspto.gov\/\">U.S.